SIMPLE: beteem
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Beteem
<hw>Be*teem"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>be-</ets> + an old verb <ets>teem</ets> to be fitting; cf. D.
<ets>betamen</ets> to beseem, G. <ets>ziemen</ets>, Goth.
<ets>gatiman</ets>, and E. <ets>tame</ets>. See <er>Tame</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give ; to bestow; to grant; to
accord; to consent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.
Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To allow; to permit; to suffer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So loving to my mother,⟦br⟧
That he might not <qex>beteem</qex> the winds of heaven⟦br⟧
Visit her face too roughly.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Betel</ent>⟦br⟧
